WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:03.000
♪ Who's gonna help when the danger overwhelms ♪

00:03.000 --> 00:05.000
♪ And the mysteries are piled high? ♪

00:05.000 --> 00:07.000
♪ Who's gonna be around, never gonna let you down ♪

00:07.000 --> 00:09.000
♪ When you're on a wild ride? ♪

00:09.000 --> 00:11.000
♪ Your friends are always by your side ♪

00:11.000 --> 00:15.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:15.000 --> 00:19.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek, he's gonna save the day ♪

00:19.000 --> 00:21.000
♪ It's Craig of the Creek ♪

00:21.000 --> 00:24.000
♪♪

00:24.000 --> 00:27.000
Please, please, please don't do this, Mom!

00:27.000 --> 00:29.000
I'll do anything! Uh, I'll clean the house.

00:29.000 --> 00:32.000
I'll wash the car and file your taxes.

00:32.000 --> 00:35.000
Just please don't leave Bernard in charge!

00:35.000 --> 00:37.000
I don't have time to argue about this, baby.

00:37.000 --> 00:39.000
Sorry, my guy, but we've got to get to the concert.

00:39.000 --> 00:42.000
♪ It's the Jelly reunion tour ♪

00:42.000 --> 00:44.000
They've been broken up for 15 years,

00:44.000 --> 00:45.000
and there's a good chance

00:45.000 --> 00:47.000
they'll break up before the end of the night,

00:47.000 --> 00:48.000
so we got to get there on time!

00:48.000 --> 00:50.000
But I don't need Bernard.

00:50.000 --> 00:52.000
I'm totally capable of taking care of myself.

00:52.000 --> 00:53.000
I'm not like Jessica.

00:53.000 --> 00:55.000
I can take care of myself!

00:55.000 --> 00:59.000
I tie my own shoes, I go to the bathroom by myself,

00:59.000 --> 01:00.000
I know which bus to take home.

01:00.000 --> 01:02.000
When Michael Finch teases me about my height,

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
I do not give him the satisfaction!

01:04.000 --> 01:06.000
Thatta girl!

01:06.000 --> 01:08.000
Are you sure you two are gonna be all right

01:08.000 --> 01:09.000
babysitting tonight?

01:09.000 --> 01:11.000
We'll be fine, Mrs. Williams!

01:11.000 --> 01:14.000
My friends and I are the most professional sitters

01:14.000 --> 01:16.000
you'll find this side of Herkleton.

01:16.000 --> 01:17.000
We're unionized.

01:17.000 --> 01:19.000
Do you see why I love this woman?

01:19.000 --> 01:21.000
This is gonna be so great, Alexis.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
It'll be like we're the mom and dad for tonight.

01:24.000 --> 01:26.000
All right, now, don't get ahead of yourself, my man.

01:26.000 --> 01:27.000
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

01:27.000 --> 01:28.000
Oh, shoot! We got to get going

01:28.000 --> 01:30.000
or we're gonna miss the opening act --

01:30.000 --> 01:31.000
Big Pocket Hank.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
He's a hip-prop comedian.

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
He freestyles about what's in his pockets.

01:35.000 --> 01:39.000
[ Sighs ] It's a lot of songs about keys and loose change.

01:39.000 --> 01:41.000
Man just needs to get a wallet.

01:41.000 --> 01:44.000
Bye, sweetie.

01:44.000 --> 01:46.000
Get along with your brother, now.

01:48.000 --> 01:51.000
That means you, too, Bernard.

01:51.000 --> 01:53.000
Well, at least it's pizza night.

01:53.000 --> 01:54.000
Sorry, little brother.

01:54.000 --> 01:56.000
There's been a change in the menu.

01:56.000 --> 01:59.000
Tonight, we're having risotto al cavolfiore.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
What?! But it's Friday!

02:01.000 --> 02:02.000
Friday is always pizza night!

02:02.000 --> 02:05.000
Well, Mom put me in charge,

02:05.000 --> 02:08.000
and Alexis and I are more than capable of cooking dinner.

02:08.000 --> 02:11.000
We got the recipe from celebrity chef couple Ash and Ajan!

02:11.000 --> 02:13.000
Bernard thought it'd make a great couple activity.

02:14.000 --> 02:16.000
Like Ash and Ajan always say,

02:16.000 --> 02:17.000
"A chef can make a meal..."

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
"But two chefs can make magic."

02:20.000 --> 02:22.000
How dare you ruin the sanctity of pizza night!

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
We will not stand for this blasphemy.

02:25.000 --> 02:27.000
Mm-hmm!

02:27.000 --> 02:29.000
Jessica! We could use some extra hands in the kitchen.

02:29.000 --> 02:31.000
Would you like to come help?

02:31.000 --> 02:33.000
[ Gasps ] Yay!

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
This is mutiny!

02:36.000 --> 02:39.000
I'm so excited about making this dish, Bernard!

02:39.000 --> 02:41.000
It's gonna be so umami.

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
Yeah! It's gonna have all the umami!

02:44.000 --> 02:47.000
And this prosciutto is going to add some great flavor text.

02:47.000 --> 02:49.000
Eugh. What's the matter?

02:49.000 --> 02:52.000
You don't like prosciutto?

02:49.000 --> 02:52.000
Pbht!

02:52.000 --> 02:54.000
Oh, come on, Craig, don't you want to be

02:54.000 --> 02:57.000
a supportive little brother and try Bernard's dish tonight?

02:57.000 --> 02:59.000
No.

02:59.000 --> 03:00.000
You know, you're lucky anyone's here to feed you at all.

03:00.000 --> 03:01.000
If you didn't know how to pour a bowl of cereal,

03:02.000 --> 03:03.000
you would've starved years ago!

03:03.000 --> 03:04.000
Bernard! Nuh-uh!

03:04.000 --> 03:06.000
I can feed myself just fine,

03:06.000 --> 03:07.000
and I'll prove it!

03:07.000 --> 03:09.000
I'm just gonna go eat dinner at the Creek!

03:09.000 --> 03:10.000
Fine! Go right ahead!

03:11.000 --> 03:14.000
Uh, j-just be back in time before sundown, okay, Craig?

03:15.000 --> 03:16.000
Don't tell me what to do!

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
You're not my mom!

03:18.000 --> 03:20.000
I'm sorry, Alexis, that was super uncalled for.

03:20.000 --> 03:22.000
We all really like you here.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
He just needs to vent.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
I'll show that chef I don't need him.

03:26.000 --> 03:29.000
I don't need anyone to take care of me.

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
What? All our emergency rations are gone!

03:32.000 --> 03:34.000
What was the emergency?

03:34.000 --> 03:35.000
We were hungry?

03:35.000 --> 03:37.000
All that's left is bird seed.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
I wouldn't go for it.

03:37.000 --> 03:39.000
[ Shrieks ]

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
It's all right, Craig.

03:41.000 --> 03:43.000
We can always just hit up the trading tree.

03:43.000 --> 03:45.000
No. If I'm gonna prove myself, then I want to do this right.

03:45.000 --> 03:48.000
I'm gonna forage for food here at the creek.

03:48.000 --> 03:51.000
And live off the land.

03:51.000 --> 03:55.000
The legends will call me Wildman Craig!

03:55.000 --> 03:58.000
I'll chop down trees for firewood.

03:58.000 --> 03:59.000
Rrrrah!

03:59.000 --> 04:03.000
And grind my own spices with my bare hands

04:03.000 --> 04:06.000
to make the tastiest dinners in the world.

04:07.000 --> 04:11.000
Wow, that Wildman Craig sounded really handsome.

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
You know, we can help you find some edible stuff.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
I've dared JP to eat all kinds of junk

04:15.000 --> 04:16.000
I've found on the ground.

04:15.000 --> 04:16.000
Yeah!

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
Aw, man, I'm glad to know that all that barfing

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
was for a good cause.

04:20.000 --> 04:23.000
Yeah, good cause.

04:23.000 --> 04:26.000
Let's find some food!

04:26.000 --> 04:28.000
Hold on.

04:28.000 --> 04:30.000
Hmm. [ Sniffs ]

04:30.000 --> 04:31.000
Ah! Here we go!

04:31.000 --> 04:32.000
Grass isn't food, man!

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
My mom and the eight doctor appointments I've had

04:35.000 --> 04:37.000
made that very clear.

04:37.000 --> 04:39.000
A-ha! Wild onions!

04:39.000 --> 04:42.000
[ Gasps ] Ohh.    [ Gasps ] Ohh.

04:42.000 --> 04:45.000
[ Gasps ] Ha ha!

04:45.000 --> 04:47.000
Oh, my gosh. I'm so sorry!

04:47.000 --> 04:48.000
I should have knocked.

04:48.000 --> 04:54.000
Ah, a plentiful harvest for Wildman Craig!

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
Guys, look! A squirrel!

04:56.000 --> 04:58.000
That noble creature is a natural forager.

04:58.000 --> 05:00.000
She'll know where to find food.

05:00.000 --> 05:02.000
Ah, this is it!

05:02.000 --> 05:04.000
They led us right to their village.

05:04.000 --> 05:08.000
And now we feast on their delicious families.

05:08.000 --> 05:09.000
JP, no!

05:09.000 --> 05:11.000
We're here to communicate with them.

05:11.000 --> 05:13.000
We'll introduce ourselves as their leaders

05:13.000 --> 05:15.000
and ask them to teach us their ways.

05:15.000 --> 05:17.000
We'll live amongst them and adapt

05:17.000 --> 05:19.000
to their self-sufficient squirrel lifestyle,

05:19.000 --> 05:21.000
keeping us well-fed and fit.

05:21.000 --> 05:23.000
Eventually, the exposure will evolve us

05:23.000 --> 05:29.000
into a new apex predator -- half-squirrel and half-human!

05:29.000 --> 05:31.000
Kelsey, we don't have time for that.

05:31.000 --> 05:32.000
I'm hungry. Oh, fine.

05:32.000 --> 05:34.000
JP, go steal some nuts for us.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.000
Wait, why me? Um...

05:37.000 --> 05:39.000
'Cause I dare you to.

05:39.000 --> 05:40.000
Oh, okay.

05:40.000 --> 05:42.000
Pardon me, little squirrely friends.

05:42.000 --> 05:45.000
Your pal JP's just lookin' for a small smackerel.

05:45.000 --> 05:47.000
[ Squirrel chattering ]

05:47.000 --> 05:48.000
Oh, bother.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.000
Aaaah! Agh!

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
They're tickling me -- violently!

05:52.000 --> 05:54.000
Uh, thanks for the diversion, JP!

05:54.000 --> 05:56.000
All right, let's get out of here!

05:56.000 --> 05:57.000
Aaah!

05:57.000 --> 05:58.000
[ Laughs ] Stop!

05:59.000 --> 06:00.000
They're crawling around in places

06:00.000 --> 06:03.000
my mom told me to stop scratchin'!

06:03.000 --> 06:05.000
Ooh, how about these crabapples?

06:05.000 --> 06:08.000
Hmm, too mushy.

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
But it looks like there are a few good ones up near the top.

06:11.000 --> 06:14.000
Yeah, but how are we supposed to get them down?

06:14.000 --> 06:18.000
I got this. [ Grunts ]

06:18.000 --> 06:19.000
Ah! My sword!

06:20.000 --> 06:21.000
[ Grunts ]

06:21.000 --> 06:24.000
No, not my staff!

06:24.000 --> 06:25.000
[ Grunts ]

06:26.000 --> 06:27.000
Wait. I-I'll get it.

06:27.000 --> 06:29.000
I'll knock it down with my shoe.

06:29.000 --> 06:31.000
[ Grunts ] Oops.

06:31.000 --> 06:34.000
Nope. Nope. Nope.

06:34.000 --> 06:36.000
Well, I ran out of things to throw.

06:36.000 --> 06:37.000
Oh, what can we do now?

06:37.000 --> 06:40.000
We're useless without our cool accessories.

06:40.000 --> 06:41.000
Hmm.

06:41.000 --> 06:43.000
Maybe it's finally time we assembled...

06:43.000 --> 06:45.000
aerial formation.

06:45.000 --> 06:47.000
[ Gasps ] But we haven't had enough practice yet.

06:47.000 --> 06:49.000
We don't know if it'll work!

06:49.000 --> 06:52.000
Huh? It will.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.000
Ready when you are, Kelsey.

06:55.000 --> 06:56.000
[ Grunts ]

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
Kelsey:  It was at that pivotal moment

06:58.000 --> 07:01.000
Kelsey realized her life would change forever.

07:01.000 --> 07:03.000
She had finally achieved the impossible feat

07:03.000 --> 07:06.000
of human fli-- Hoof.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
Both: Yeah!

07:10.000 --> 07:11.000
Craig: This is perfect.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.000
We don't need no snooty-proshooty to make a meal.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.000
Let's get prepping.

07:17.000 --> 07:22.000
Ah, the pure, untainted waters of a slip 'n' flip.

07:22.000 --> 07:24.000
Wheeee!

07:24.000 --> 07:28.000
Feel the might of my PVC pulverizer!

07:28.000 --> 07:29.000
Rah!

07:29.000 --> 07:31.000
Huh? [ Groans ]

07:31.000 --> 07:33.000
[ Grunting ]

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
[ Sighs ]

07:35.000 --> 07:39.000
Will...you... break...al-ready?!

07:39.000 --> 07:40.000
[ Humming ]

07:40.000 --> 07:48.000
♪♪

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
Hey, Kelsey, you got those acorns?

07:50.000 --> 07:54.000
With an aid of a noble rock, I was able to crack...

07:54.000 --> 07:55.000
one. Oh.

07:55.000 --> 07:58.000
Um, h-how about those crab apples, JP?

07:58.000 --> 07:59.000
Oh, yeah. No.

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
Uh, I threw those in the creek.

07:59.000 --> 08:01.000
Well, why?

08:01.000 --> 08:03.000
I'm pretty sure they're evil,

08:03.000 --> 08:05.000
and I'm pretty sure I'm allergic.

08:05.000 --> 08:06.000
Okay. Okay.

08:06.000 --> 08:08.000
Um, uh, we still have the onions.

08:08.000 --> 08:11.000
We can make onion soup!

08:11.000 --> 08:14.000
♪♪

08:14.000 --> 08:17.000
Hmm, I'm gonna be honest.

08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
Kinda just looks like dirty onion water.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.000
[ Slurps ]

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
So, how's it taste?

08:25.000 --> 08:26.000
[ Groans ]

08:26.000 --> 08:28.000
Like dirty onion water.

08:28.000 --> 08:29.000
Aww...

08:29.000 --> 08:30.000
who am I kidding?

08:31.000 --> 08:33.000
I'm not capable of taking care of myself.

08:33.000 --> 08:35.000
I'm not even capable of making dinner.

08:35.000 --> 08:38.000
Aw, poor Craiggory.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
[ Horn blows ]

08:40.000 --> 08:41.000
You guys better head home.

08:42.000 --> 08:43.000
Yeah.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.000
I should probably put some ointment on this.

08:45.000 --> 08:46.000
♪♪

08:47.000 --> 08:48.000
Duane: Craig!

08:48.000 --> 08:52.000
Welcome back to "So You Think You Can Take Care of Yourself?"

08:52.000 --> 08:57.000
Tonight in Responsibility Stadium, we have my sons!

08:57.000 --> 08:58.000
And Alexis.

08:58.000 --> 09:01.000
Bernard, Alexis, what are you presenting?

09:01.000 --> 09:04.000
We made Risotto Al blah, blah, blah.

09:05.000 --> 09:06.000
It's Italian.

09:06.000 --> 09:09.000
It's delicious! It's delicious!

09:09.000 --> 09:12.000
You are not only capable of taking care of yourselves,

09:12.000 --> 09:14.000
but the whole family!

09:14.000 --> 09:16.000
How about you, Craig?

09:16.000 --> 09:17.000
What do you have?

09:17.000 --> 09:20.000
Uh, dirty onion water.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
Ew, gross!

09:22.000 --> 09:25.000
You are incapable of taking care of yourself!

09:25.000 --> 09:29.000
Your brother will have to babysit you forever!

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
♪♪

09:31.000 --> 09:33.000
No!

09:33.000 --> 09:35.000
Alexis: Sorry!

09:35.000 --> 09:36.000
It's fine! Just hurry!

09:36.000 --> 09:37.000
I got to keep stirring!

09:37.000 --> 09:41.000
♪♪

09:41.000 --> 09:42.000
[ Groans ]

09:42.000 --> 09:45.000
It doesn't look like the picture at all.

09:45.000 --> 09:46.000
[ Sighs ]

09:46.000 --> 09:48.000
I'm a failure.

09:48.000 --> 09:49.000
Hey.

09:49.000 --> 09:51.000
My parents put me in charge.

09:51.000 --> 09:54.000
I'm supposed to be the responsible big brother,

09:54.000 --> 09:57.000
and I just totally failed.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
I'm not capable of cooking a fancy risotto.

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
I'm not capable of cooking anything.

10:02.000 --> 10:06.000
The table is all set. I'm ready to eat!

10:06.000 --> 10:07.000
Ugh, what do we do?

10:07.000 --> 10:08.000
We got to serve them something,

10:08.000 --> 10:10.000
or else they'll kick me out of the union!

10:10.000 --> 10:11.000
I cannot have that.

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
I'm the sergeant at arms.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
Okay! Here ya go.

10:15.000 --> 10:16.000
Hmm.                        Hmm.

10:16.000 --> 10:19.000
This is dinner?

10:19.000 --> 10:20.000
Hmm.

10:20.000 --> 10:23.000
B-Bon appetit. [ Chuckles nervously ]

10:23.000 --> 10:26.000
Uh...

10:27.000 --> 10:28.000
Mmm.

10:28.000 --> 10:31.000
It's actually... pretty good.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.000
R-Really?

10:33.000 --> 10:35.000
The heck are you talking about, Craig?

10:35.000 --> 10:37.000
Just add a little bit of cheese on top!

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
There, try that.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
Ahh...

10:41.000 --> 10:43.000
Mmm, tastes like cheese!

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
Hmm.

10:45.000 --> 10:49.000
The cheese definitely gives the dish a robust nutty flavor.

10:49.000 --> 10:50.000
There's room for improvement,

10:50.000 --> 10:54.000
but I think we did pretty good for our first try.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
Yeah, good job, Bernard.

10:56.000 --> 10:57.000
Thanks.

10:58.000 --> 10:59.000
[ Groans ]

10:59.000 --> 11:01.000
Pass the cheese, please!

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
♪ When it's time to go to bed ♪

11:04.000 --> 11:09.000
♪ I know I don't have to feel alone ♪

11:09.000 --> 11:12.000
♪ 'Cause I'll see you tomorrow ♪

11:12.000 --> 11:14.000
♪ At the creek ♪

11:14.000 --> 11:16.000
Just like I drew it.

11:16.000 --> 11:19.000
♪♪
